cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the information encoded in the weights of a deep neural network and how it affects the response of the network to future data. It also introduces a new notion of information in the weights and relates it to generalization and invariance. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with deep neural networks and their weights. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible sub-category as the paper introduces a new notion of information in the weights and relates it to known information measures such as Shannon Mutual Information and Fisher Information. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks and the paper discusses the information encoded in the weights of these networks.
